To send the user an email when they successfully book an MK, you can use an email service like SendGrid or Nodemailer. You'll need to set up an account with one of these services and obtain an API key or credentials to access the email service.

Once you have the necessary credentials, you can use a library like `nodemailer` to send an email to the user when they book an MK. Here's an example implementation:

1. Install `nodemailer` using npm:

   ```
   npm install nodemailer
   ```

2. Set up `nodemailer` with your email service credentials:

   ```
   const nodemailer = require('nodemailer');

   // create reusable transporter object using the default SMTP transport
   let transporter = nodemailer.createTransport({
     host: 'smtp.gmail.com',
     port: 465,
     secure: true, // true for 465, false for other ports
     auth: {
       user: YOUR_EMAIL_ADDRESS, // generated ethereal user
       pass: YOUR_EMAIL_PASSWORD, // generated ethereal password
     },
   });
   ```

3. When the user successfully books an MK, send them an email using `nodemailer`:

   ```
   const bookingInfo = {
     // add relevant booking information here
   };

   // send mail with defined transport object
   let info = await transporter.sendMail({
     from: '"My App" <info@myapp.com>', // sender address
     to: 'user@example.com', // list of receivers
     subject: 'MK Booking Confirmation', // Subject line
     text: `Dear User,\n\nThank you for booking an MK! Here is your booking information: ${JSON.stringify(bookingInfo)}\n\nWe look forward to seeing you!\n\nBest,\nThe My App Team`, // plain text body
     html: `<p>Dear User,</p><p>Thank you for booking an MK! Here is your booking information:</p><pre>${JSON.stringify(
       bookingInfo,
       null,
       2
     )}</pre><p>We look forward to seeing you!</p><p>Best,</p><p>The My App Team</p>`, // html body
   });

   console.log('Message sent: %s', info.messageId);
   ```

   In this example, we're sending a plain text and HTML email using the `sendMail` method of the `transporter` object. You'll need to replace the sender and recipient addresses, subject line, message text/html, and booking information with your own values.

